        "duration": 2.324
    },
    {
        "text": "Just one.",
        "start": 225.331,
        "duration": 1.359
    },
    {
        "text": "So remember, if there’s just one, we have to put ‘a’.",
        "start": 226.69,
        "duration": 5.22
    },
    {
        "text": "“I’m a student.”",
        "start": 231.91,
        "duration": 3.163
    },
    {
        "text": "Let’s look at the next one.",
        "start": 235.073,
        "duration": 2.196
    },
    {
        "text": "“They are student”.",
        "start": 237.269,
        "duration": 2.731
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay.",
        "start": 240.0,
        "duration": 1.492
    },
    {
        "text": "This one says, “They are”.",
        "start": 241.492,
        "duration": 2.829
    },
    {
        "text": "This means there is more than one.",
        "start": 244.321,
        "duration": 2.675
    },
    {
        "text": "More than one student.",
        "start": 246.996,
        "duration": 2.14
    },
    {
        "text": "So, what do we have to do?",
        "start": 249.136,
        "duration": 2.544
    },
    {
        "text": "We have to say “They are….",
        "start": 251.68,
        "duration": 3.628
    },
    {
        "text": "students”.",
        "start": 255.308,
        "duration": 1.762
    },
    {
        "text": "We have to put an ‘s’ to show there’s\nmore than one student.",
        "start": 257.07,
        "duration": 6.015
    },
    {
        "text": "“She aren’t a baby.”",
